{
  "article_id": "IllustratedAmerican1892",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "THE lonely wind-swept island of San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", eighty miles off the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura County, California",
        "entity_key": "co_ventura",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", is known as the \"Isle of Skulls.\" A most peculiar name, but judging from recent reports of archæologists, who are now busy gathering the relics of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a strange extinct race",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is most appropriately called. "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "its erstwhile inhabitants",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "have a history so curious that it is difficult of comprehension."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1835 "
      },
      {
        "text": "the",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "padres",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of Santa Barbara,",
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "learning that there were but "
      },
      {
        "text": "sixteen persons left of the strange Indian race",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "once living there, determined to rescue them from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island.",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "They went over in "
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and succeeded, as they thought, in getting all on board. At the last moment "
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "returned for "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and one of the frequent storms of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "springing up, "
      },
      {
        "text": "the sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was driven away without her. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The sloop",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "went on the rocks of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Conception",
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and all on board were lost."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Sixteen years later ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "two men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "gni",
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "went from the coast on ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to hunt otter off ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". On landing they were, like Crusoe, astonished to discover human footprints in the sand. They saw no one, however, and a storm compelled them to put to sea.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "It was two years thereafter that ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the adventurous captain",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", revolving in his mind the sight of the footprints in ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the uncanny island",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", determined to go and discover, and bring over ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lonely woman",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of whom he had vaguely heard.",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "accompanied him, and at length they saw on the surf-beaten shore ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "with long tawny hair dressed in a queer garb of colored bird-skins, and scraping, with a bone knife, the blubber from a seal.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "When suddenly surrounded and confronted she did not appear in the least afraid, but smiled, and then falling on her knees prayed to the sun. When by signs she was made to understand, and that she was to accompany her captors, she made no resistance.",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "They reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "across the rough sea, and the first thing "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "saw was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. S. L. Shaw",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", now eighty years old and yet living there, riding a horse. She had never seen nor heard of any object like it, and thought "
      },
      {
        "text": "the man",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and horse were one, and she knelt on the shore and offered her devotions to it. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Two weeks afterward ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant of rock-ribbed, tempest-tossed San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "died from eating food to which she was unaccustomed, furnished by ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her rescuers",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and the curtain fell on ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "forever.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Had "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "rescued, then fifty-two years old, not died, a story passing strange would no doubt have been told of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the race so long hemmed in by the waste of waters about",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". As it is, much of the story is shrouded in mystery forever. Her dress of red and blue feathers, a wonderful creation of barbaric hands, was sent to "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Pope",
        "entity_key": "pop",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rome",
        "entity_key": "ci_rom",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "As far back as the memory of man runs, hundreds of white skeletons have dotted the valleys and hill-sides, and strange utensils of serpentine[,] sandstone and steatite are constantly being found there among the human bones. Relic hunters have gathered mortars, pestles, ollas, toy steatite canoes, and other curious things there for some years past, and shipped them to various Eastern and European universities.",
        "tropes": [
          7
        ]
      }
    ]
  ]
}